---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const faqData = [
  {
    question: "Does Costco hot dog have nitrates?",
    answer: "Yes. Costco hot dogs contain sodium nitrite as a preservative to prevent spoilage and maintain color."
  },
  {
    question: "Are nitrates in hot dogs harmful?",
    answer: "The FDA regulates nitrite levels in processed meats. Occasional consumption is generally considered safe for most people."
  }
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Does Costco Hot Dog Have Nitrates?"
  description="Yes — Costco hot dogs contain sodium nitrite. Learn about nitrate content and health considerations."
  type="faq"
  faqData={faqData}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-8 text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-yellow-700 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide">Answer</p>
      <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-yellow-800 mt-2">Yes</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-700 mt-2">Contains sodium nitrite</p>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Does Costco Hot Dog Have Nitrates?</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Understanding nitrate content and what it means for your health.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Sodium Nitrite</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Costco hot dogs contain sodium nitrite, a common preservative used in cured meats. It serves two purposes: preventing bacterial growth (especially botulism) and maintaining the characteristic pink color of cured meats.</p>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Health Considerations</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">The World Health Organization has classified processed meats as carcinogenic when consumed in large quantities over long periods. However, occasional consumption of hot dogs as part of a balanced diet is generally considered low-risk for most people.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
